HEADWORD: Alkahest
<hw>Al"ka*hest</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>alchahest</ets>, F. <ets>alcahest</ets>, a word that has an Arabic
appearance, but was probably arbitrarily formed by Paracelsus.]</ety>
<def>The fabled ⟦ldquo⟧universal solvent⟦rdquo⟧ of the alchemists; a
menstruum capable of dissolving all bodies.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Al`ka*hes"tic</wf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

